{
  "texts": [
    "to red-team a model).It might make sense for the ethics board to rely on outside expertise if they have limited expertise or time.",
    "They could also use it to get a more objective perspective, as information provided to them by the company can be biased (Sect. 6.2).",
    "However, the company might use the same sources of outside expertise.",
    "For example, if a company is open to a thirdparty audit, it would commission the audit directly (why would it ask the ethics board to do it on its behalf?).",
    "In such cases, the ethics board would merely \"double-check\" the company's or the third party's work."
  ]
}